A section of fence is shown below.  What is the length of the gap between each post?

\begin{center}
\includegraphics[scale=0.4]{images/ds_l2.png}
\end{center}
}

\textbf{Answer:} One post and gap have a length of 57 cm, so two gaps and two posts have a length of 114 cm.  Subtracting 114 from 131 gives the length of a post: 17 cm.  Subtracting 17 from 57 gives a length of $\boxed{40}$ cm for the gap.
